    <div class="container">
        <section id="introduction">
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>
                As global water concerns grow, civil engineering must take the lead in developing new solutions to assure long-term water management. "Flowing Forward" strives to advocate for revolutionary practices that protect our water supplies for future generations.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section id="objectives">
            <h2>Objectives of the Advocacy</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Innovate with Green Infrastructure:</strong> Encourage the use of green roofs, bioswales, and rain gardens to effectively manage stormwater, lowering runoff and improving local ecosystems.</li>
                <li><strong>Implement Water Recycling and Reuse:</strong> Advocate for greywater recycling and rainfall harvesting technologies, reducing reliance on fresh water and promoting sustainable use.</li>
                <li><strong>Revitalize Aging Water Systems:</strong> Support projects to modernize obsolete water infrastructure, reduce leaks, and improve distribution efficiency to maintain reliable access.</li>
                <li><strong>Enhance Flood Resilience:</strong> Develop and implement comprehensive flood management methods, including wetlands restoration and permeable surfaces, to protect communities from floods.</li>
                <li><strong>Leverage Smart Technology:</strong> Deploy smart water management systems that use sensors and data analytics to monitor water levels in real time and allocate resources efficiently.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="conclusions">
            <h2>Conclusions</h2>
            <p>
                "Flowing Forward" emphasizes civil engineering's important role in addressing water issues. By implementing creative and sustainable techniques, we can safeguard our communities' and the environment's water security and health. Together, we can build a resilient water system that benefits both people and the environment.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section id="resources">
